ccom-review.benefits:

      and Renaissance Hotels and Resorts on weekends, this card entitles you to complimentary breakfast and $100 off your next stay. Car rental loss and damage insurance, and travel accident insurance is also available, as well as access to a “global assist”
      hotline.
ccom-review.who-should-apply: Individuals who travel frequently and use credit regularly for everyday purchases may benefit from the travel rewards. Members who pay their bill in full regularly each month will also avoid paying interest fees.

ccom-review.overview:
The READYdebit Prepaid Visa Card is a debit card and is designed to give consumers with poor credit the flexibility and convenience of paying with a traditional credit card but without all the headaches that come with traditional cards. The READYdebit Prepaid Visa Card is a useful tool if you want a more secure spending option than cash, but don't have access to credit, or don't want to use a credit card.

You're eligible for this card regardless of your credit situation, even if you have no credit.  All you have to do is load the card with money, and it's ready to go.

This card won't help you build credit, since your spending and payment activity on a prepaid debit card are not reported to the credit bureaus.  But it does provide a secure spending alternative to cash, and you won't be charged interest on your purchases. And because it's a prepaid card, you won't be able to spend over your "limit" - which is the amount you have on deposit.
ccom-review.credit-standing: The READYdebit Prepaid Visa Card is open to anyone, regardless of their credit history. Consumers with no established credit can also secure this card.
ccom-review.rates:
Expect to pay a one-time set-up fee of $9.95, then a monthly service fee of $9.95 - which among other things, allows you free PIN transactions and balance inquiries.

You have unlimited access to automated customer service.  If you want to talk to a live customer service representative, it's free one time per month; after the initial free monthly call, it's $2 per call.
ccom-review.benefits:
When you set up your account online, you have the option of setting up direct deposit or bank transfers, free of charge.  You can also choose to load it at participating retail stores such as Wal-Mart, Walgreens, Rite Aid or anywhere you see the Visa ReadyLink logo.

There are no overdraft fees or bounced check fees with the READYdebit Prepaid Visa Card.  You can also send money from one card to another for free, and you can use it for online bill-paying.

In terms of security, the money you load onto the card is FDIC-insured, and your purchases are covered by Visa Zero Fraud Liability protection.
ccom-review.who-should-apply: Anyone that would prefer the convenience of paying with a credit card but not the high fees and interest rates that usually accompany such a card.  It's also a great option for consumers that are unable to open a checking account or have very poor credit. In fact, consumers with all types of credit, including no credit, are eligible for this card.

ccom-review.rewards: Though no special deals or incentives apply to the AccountNow Gold Visa, customers will benefit from convenient access to online services and free bill pay.

ccom-review.rates: The AccountNow Gold Visa does carry some fees, but annual percentage rates do not apply. There is no application fee, but cardholders will be charged a $2.50 fee each time they make an ATM withdrawal. Account holders will also be subject to a $9.95 one-time Gold Privilege fee the first time they load money to their card. Users may also be charged a $9.95 monthly usage fee; however, this fee will be waived for those who load $3,000 or more on to their prepaid product in one month.
ccom-review.benefits: The AccountNow Gold Visa removes the hassle of lengthly application processes and credit checks. Cardholders can also spend the amount loaded onto their card without the fear of incurring large amounts of interest charges or fees and penalties. The prepaid card provides the benefits of a debit card by allowing users to withdraw funds via ATM - for a small fee - but carries the traditional fraud liability protections of a conventional credit card.
ccom-review.who-should-apply: Prepaid products are geared towards consumers that want the convenience of carrying plastic without the hassle of changing APRs and costly penalty fees.
